"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT client.client_id)\nFROM client\nJOIN disp ON client.client_id = disp.client_id\nJOIN card ON disp.disp_id = card.disp_id\nWHERE client.gender = 'F' AND card.type = 'junior';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct female customers (`client.client_id`) who have a junior credit card. It joins the `client`, `disp`, and `card` tables using the foreign key relationships and applies the conditions specified in the question and evidence."